.\" @(#)dtoc.w	1.1
dtoc [\fIdirectory\fR]; directory table of contents
.sp
Output is a list of all readable subdirectories beginning at \fIdirectory\fR.
If no \fIdirectory\fR is given, the list begins at the current directory.
The output is in the form of a textual table of contents readable by \fIvtoc\fR.
The number of nondirectory files in each directory is indicated in the mark
field of the table of contents.
